Package com.tractrac.subscription.lib.api

Interface IRaceSubscriber

All Superinterfaces:
ISubscriber
public interface IRaceSubscriber extends ISubscriber

This interface is used to add subscriptions for a IRace object.

Author:
Jorge Piera Llodrá

  • Method Details

    • subscribePositions

      void subscribePositions(IPositionListener listener)
      Subscribes to competitor positions for a given Race. It uses the tracking start time and the tracking end time as time interval to receive positions.

      The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to the given listener, as they are received.

      Parameters:
      listener - the listener to receive the positions.

    • subscribePositions

      void subscribePositions(IPositionListener listener, UUID... classIds)
      Subscribes to competitor positions for a given Race and class(es). It uses the tracking start time and the tracking end time as time interval to receive positions.

      The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to the given listener, as they are received.

      Parameters:
      listener - the listener to receive the positions.
      classIds - the class ids

    • subscribePositions

      void subscribePositions(IPositionListener listener, long fromTime, long toTime)
      Subscribes to competitor positions for a given Race.

      The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to the given listener, as they are received.

      Parameters:
      listener - the listener to receive the positions.
      fromTime - stored positions (if supported) will be requested from this time and forward. The value 0 is allowed and means all historic data.
      toTime - The value Long.MAXVALUE means all data in the future

    • subscribePositions

      toTime - The value Long.MAXVALUE means all data in the future

    • subscribePositionedItemPositions

      void subscribePositionedItemPositions(IPositionedItemPositionListener listener)
      Subscribes to control positions for the race.

      The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to the given listener, as they are received.

      It also returns the static positions using the IRace.getTrackingStartTime() as the value for the position time. These positions are sent before to start to send the dynamic positions.

      Parameters:
      listener - the listener to receive the positions.

    • subscribePositionedItemPositions

      void subscribePositionedItemPositions(IPositionedItemPositionListener listener, long fromTime, long toTime)
      Subscribes to positioned item positions for the race, also retrieving historic data.

      The method returns immediately and the positions are subsequently sent to the given listener, as they are received.

      It also returns the static positions using the IRace.getTrackingStartTime() as the value for the position time. These positions are sent before to start to send the dynamic positions.

      Parameters:
      listener - the listener to receive the positions.
      fromTime - stored positions (if supported) will be requested from this time and forward. The value 0 is allowed and means all historic data.
      toTime - The value Long.MAXVALUE means all data in the future
